# To build xskat:

1. Ensure you have CMake installed on your system.
   (e.g., sudo apt-get install cmake on Debian/Ubuntu)

2. Create a build directory and navigate into it:
   mkdir build
   cd build

3. Run CMake to configure the project:
   cmake ..

4. Compile the program:
   make

# Start the program
./xskat

# To install the program (optional, may require root privileges):
# After building, you can typically run:
# sudo make install
# (This will install xskat and its man page if defined in CMakeLists.txt)
